âœ… ABSTRACT

The Student Record Management System is a simple console-based application developed using the C programming language. The purpose of this project is to manage basic student information such as roll number, name, and marks. The system allows users to add new student records, display all records, and search for a student by roll number. This project demonstrates the use of structures, functions, arrays, and decision-making statements in C programming.

âœ… PROBLEM DEFINITION

Managing student records manually is time-consuming and error-prone. There is a need for a simple system that can efficiently store and access student data. This project is designed to provide a basic digital solution for handling student records using fundamental concepts of C programming.

